That just shows so much of
the transformational aspects

00:37:07.292 --> 00:37:11.697 align:middle line:84%
of laughter and you make people
laugh for a living but it is,

00:37:11.697 --> 00:37:15.934 align:middle line:84%
it is innately what is in
every single relationship

00:37:15.934 --> 00:37:19.571 align:middle line:90%
that we have is laughter.

00:37:19.571 --> 00:37:21.707 align:middle line:84%
You spent some time
with a wonderful couple

00:37:21.707 --> 00:37:23.241 align:middle line:90%
that you learned a lot from.

00:37:23.241 --> 00:37:26.078 align:middle line:90%
Tell me about them.

00:37:26.078 --> 00:37:27.446 align:middle line:90%
>> YS: They're amazing.

00:37:27.446 --> 00:37:32.150 align:middle line:84%
They, I actually saw them on
the Tonight Show with Jay Leno

00:37:32.150 --> 00:37:36.188 align:middle line:84%
and they just celebrated
their 75th wedding anniversary

00:37:36.188 --> 00:37:39.825 align:middle line:84%
and I don't know anybody
who'd celebrate that kind

00:37:39.825 --> 00:37:42.461 align:middle line:84%
of anniversary so I
reached out to them

00:37:42.461 --> 00:37:48.533 align:middle line:84%
and they were very receptive and
I was doing a show, a talk show,

00:37:48.533 --> 00:37:53.538 align:middle line:84%
in Branson and I invited them to
come to Branson and they agreed

00:37:53.538 --> 00:38:00.145 align:middle line:84%
to come, and we sent a limo to
pick them up from the airport

00:38:00.145 --> 00:38:03.982 align:middle line:84%
and the driver was told
there would be a couple

00:38:03.982 --> 00:38:05.650 align:middle line:90%
with their son.

00:38:05.650 --> 00:38:07.919 align:middle line:90%
So he brought a baby car seat.

00:38:07.919 --> 00:38:14.593 align:middle line:84%
He said how old is
the son, they said 70,

00:38:14.593 --> 00:38:17.496 align:middle line:90%
so we might need one soon.

00:38:17.496 --> 00:38:21.666 align:middle line:90%
But anyway, so they got there

00:38:21.666 --> 00:38:25.237 align:middle line:84%
and when I saw them they were
giggling, they were laughing,

00:38:25.237 --> 00:38:27.339 align:middle line:84%
they were holding
hands and I said

00:38:27.339 --> 00:38:28.807 align:middle line:90%
to them, what is your secret?

00:38:28.807 --> 00:38:30.909 align:middle line:84%
They said we're afraid
to fall down.

00:38:30.909 --> 00:38:33.278 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: [Laughing] They're
holding hands to stay up.

00:38:33.278 --> 00:38:37.015 align:middle line:84%
>> YS: Yes and they're adorable
so I, we became good friends.

00:38:37.015 --> 00:38:39.484 align:middle line:84%
They live in Thousand
Oaks California

00:38:39.484 --> 00:38:40.685 align:middle line:90%
and I'm friends with them.

00:38:40.685 --> 00:38:45.190 align:middle line:84%
I actually am going to
dinner with them tomorrow.

00:38:45.190 --> 00:38:46.458 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Now what did
you learn from them?

00:38:46.458 --> 00:38:49.261 align:middle line:90%
What was the biggest take away?

00:38:49.261 --> 00:38:56.001 align:middle line:84%
>> YS: All of this what I
am sharing about the gift,

00:38:56.001 --> 00:39:01.706 align:middle line:84%
came from conversations with
them because of when I was,

00:39:01.706 --> 00:39:06.144 align:middle line:84%
you know, I said to them
how, how did you get this?

00:39:06.144 --> 00:39:10.882 align:middle line:84%
You sustained this
honeymoon for all these years

00:39:10.882 --> 00:39:13.685 align:middle line:90%
and I said what made it?

00:39:13.685 --> 00:39:15.454 align:middle line:84%
And she said, we
didn't understand this

00:39:15.454 --> 00:39:18.223 align:middle line:84%
because when we got
married it was scary,

00:39:18.223 --> 00:39:19.524 align:middle line:90%
it was depression time.

00:39:19.524 --> 00:39:22.727 align:middle line:90%
We had no money, we were young

00:39:22.727 --> 00:39:27.833 align:middle line:84%
and my husband wanted
me to be happy.

00:39:27.833 --> 00:39:31.336 align:middle line:84%
He made a promise
and he said I know

00:39:31.336 --> 00:39:33.538 align:middle line:84%
that you're happy
when you're laughing.

00:39:33.538 --> 00:39:37.342 align:middle line:90%
So he said, so he told me,

00:39:37.342 --> 00:39:40.579 align:middle line:84%
he said I knew what would
make her happy is a fur coat

00:39:40.579 --> 00:39:43.081 align:middle line:84%
and we didn't have any
money so he said I went out

00:39:43.081 --> 00:39:44.816 align:middle line:90%
and bought her a mouse trap,

00:39:44.816 --> 00:39:48.787 align:middle line:84%
and the little card
said, it's a starter kit.

00:39:48.787 --> 00:39:49.921 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: [Laughing]

00:39:49.921 --> 00:39:51.790 align:middle line:84%
>> YS: And she said they
didn't get the fur coat

00:39:51.790 --> 00:39:54.025 align:middle line:84%
but I got something better,
I got the gift of laughter

00:39:54.025 --> 00:39:55.327 align:middle line:90%
and it's lasted a lifetime.

00:39:55.327 --> 00:39:58.864 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Let's take a look at
this beautiful couple and,

00:39:58.864 --> 00:40:02.133 align:middle line:84%
and learn a little
something from them.

00:40:02.133 --> 00:40:11.209 align:middle line:90%
[ Video Playing ]

00:43:42.887 --> 00:43:45.290 align:middle line:84%
So you've spent a lot
of time with this couple

00:43:45.290 --> 00:43:51.262 align:middle line:84%
and are you still
continuing to learn from them?

00:43:51.262 --> 00:43:54.933 align:middle line:84%
>> YS: Oh yeah, oh yeah, every
time I see them I am amazed

00:43:54.933 --> 00:44:00.305 align:middle line:84%
because they just celebrated now
their 80th wedding anniversary

00:44:00.305 --> 00:44:07.779 align:middle line:84%
and it's just so heartwarming
to see how caring they are

00:44:07.779 --> 00:44:12.784 align:middle line:84%
and her health is getting
pretty, not so good anymore

00:44:12.784 --> 00:44:16.020 align:middle line:84%
and he's still driving,
he's still,

00:44:16.020 --> 00:44:18.289 align:middle line:84%
he just celebrated
his 100th birthday.

00:44:18.289 --> 00:44:18.823 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: What?

00:44:18.823 --> 00:44:19.924 align:middle line:90%
>> YS: Yeah.

00:44:19.924 --> 00:44:24.929 align:middle line:84%
He did, on December
nine and he called me

00:44:24.929 --> 00:44:26.731 align:middle line:90%
and he said Yakov we're going

00:44:26.731 --> 00:44:29.634 align:middle line:84%
to be celebrating my 100th
birthday could you come be a

00:44:29.634 --> 00:44:30.835 align:middle line:90%
part of this?

00:44:30.835 --> 00:44:32.570 align:middle line:84%
And I said I'd love to but
I have shows in Branson

00:44:32.570 --> 00:44:37.208 align:middle line:84%
until December 9th so I
won't be able to make it,

00:44:37.208 --> 00:44:41.880 align:middle line:84%
and he goes well we can
postpone the celebration.

00:44:41.880 --> 00:44:46.418 align:middle line:84%
I said if I was 100 I would
not postpone the celebration.

00:44:46.418 --> 00:44:49.387 align:middle line:84%
So, but they did postpone it,
I came and spent some time

00:44:49.387 --> 00:44:51.956 align:middle line:84%
with them and his daughter
was sharing with me

00:44:51.956 --> 00:44:53.858 align:middle line:84%
that she's nervous
that he's driving

00:44:53.858 --> 00:44:56.327 align:middle line:90%
so she took away his car keys.

00:44:56.327 --> 00:44:58.797 align:middle line:84%
So he went and bought
his new car.

00:44:58.797 --> 00:45:00.365 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: [Laughing] At 100?

00:45:00.365 --> 00:45:01.733 align:middle line:90%
>> YS: 100, yes.

00:45:01.733 --> 00:45:03.835 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Well I mean this
just goes to show you

00:45:03.835 --> 00:45:07.305 align:middle line:84%
that laughter leads to
longevity if anything.

00:45:07.305 --> 00:45:07.939 align:middle line:90%
>> YS: That's true.

00:45:07.939 --> 00:45:09.073 align:middle line:90%
That is true.

00:45:09.073 --> 00:45:11.075 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So let me ask you
about your perspective

00:45:11.075 --> 00:45:13.845 align:middle line:84%
on relationships and
especially in this country

00:45:13.845 --> 00:45:17.148 align:middle line:84%
and as opposed to, I
mean was divorce the norm

00:45:17.148 --> 00:45:18.883 align:middle line:90%
or not the norm where you lived?

00:45:18.883 --> 00:45:19.517 align:middle line:90%
>> YS: No.

00:45:19.517 --> 00:45:20.652 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Not at all.

00:45:20.652 --> 00:45:23.321 align:middle line:84%
>> YS: In Russia I
honestly don't know anyone

00:45:23.321 --> 00:45:25.390 align:middle line:90%
who had gone through divorce.

00:45:25.390 --> 00:45:28.893 align:middle line:84%
All my classmates,
everybody stayed together

00:45:28.893 --> 00:45:33.264 align:middle line:84%
but it was also survival
environment

00:45:33.264 --> 00:45:36.067 align:middle line:84%
where people teamed
together, not just them

00:45:36.067 --> 00:45:39.470 align:middle line:84%
but the whole family
to just find food,

00:45:39.470 --> 00:45:41.940 align:middle line:90%
find shelter, all of that.

00:45:41.940 --> 00:45:43.908 align:middle line:90%
We are way past that.

00:45:43.908 --> 00:45:47.612 align:middle line:84%
America, we live in
a comfort society,

00:45:47.612 --> 00:45:50.081 align:middle line:90%
we have all of our needs met.

00:45:50.081 --> 00:45:56.054 align:middle line:84%
